   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In Tuner, click on the <uicontrol>Settings</uicontrol> tab
and click on <uicontrol>Edit Settings</uicontrol>.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tuner1_0000148976.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <p>In the column <uicontrol>Systems Settings</uicontrol> you
see the present settings of the UPS.</p>
               <p>In the column <uicontrol>User Settings</uicontrol> you can configure the UPS settings. Changed
values in the <uicontrol>User Settings</uicontrol> column are red.</p>
               <p/>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p/>
            <ul>
               <li>Configure the setting parameters in the <uicontrol>User Settings</uicontrol> column as needed and click on the <uicontrol>Send</uicontrol> button
to send them to the UPS.<fig>
                     <image href="../Images/tuner_send_0000148975.jpg"
                            scalefit="yes"
                            placement="inline"/>
                  </fig>
               </li>
               <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Export</uicontrol> button to export
the settings as a binary (BIN) file. <fig>
                     <image href="../Images/tuner_export_0000148974.jpg"
                            scalefit="yes"
                            placement="inline"/>
                  </fig>
               </li>
               <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Import</uicontrol> button and browse
to a stored settings file on your laptop to import these settings
to the <uicontrol>User Settings</uicontrol> column. <fig>
                     <image href="../Images/tuner_import_0000148973.jpg"
                            scalefit="yes"
                            placement="inline"/>
                  </fig>
               </li>
               <li>Click on the <uicontrol>Reset</uicontrol> button to restore
all the settings in the <uicontrol>User Settings</uicontrol> column
to match the settings in the <uicontrol>Systems Settings</uicontrol> column.</li>
            </ul>
         </li>
      </ol>
